"script": "Could you survive jumping from a plane with no parachute? Surprisingly, the falling part won't kill you. After about fifteen seconds, you stop speeding up and drift down at a steady 120 miles an hour. The problem is the very last second. Hit concrete, and your body stops in an instant while your organs keep moving. But people have actually lived through this. The trick is what you land on. Deep snow, a marsh, or thick trees can stretch that deadly stop into a survivable one. So it's not the fall that decides your fate. It's the final inch.",
